hdWGCNA basics

snRNA-seq 

# single-cell analysis package
library(Seurat)

# plotting and data science packages
library(tidyverse)
library(cowplot)
library(patchwork)

# co-expression network analysis packages:
library(WGCNA)
library(hdWGCNA)

# using the cowplot theme for ggplot
theme_set(theme_cowplot())

# 
seurat_ref <- readRDS('hdWGCNA_object.rds')

1 Compute correlations

ModuleTraitCorrelation

Variables that can be used

  • 2
  • disease stage healthy, stage 1, stage 2, stage 3 factor

Variables that can not be used

  • Sample ID module-trait 
# convert sex to factor
seurat_obj$msex <- as.factor(seurat_obj$msex)

# convert age_death to numeric
seurat_obj$age_death <- as.numeric(seurat_obj$age_death)

# list of traits to correlate
cur_traits <- c('braaksc', 'pmi', 'msex', 'age_death', 'doublet_scores', 'nCount_RNA', 'nFeature_RNA', 'total_counts_mt')

seurat_obj <- ModuleTraitCorrelation(
  seurat_obj,
  traits = cur_traits,
  group.by='cell_type'
)

2 Plot Correlation Heatmap

PlotModuleTraitCorrelation patchwork 

PlotModuleTraitCorrelation(
  seurat_obj,
  label = 'fdr',
  label_symbol = 'stars',
  text_size = 2,
  text_digits = 2,
  text_color = 'white',
  high_color = 'yellow',
  mid_color = 'black',
  low_color = 'purple',
  plot_max = 0.2,
  combine=TRUE
)
